.name
Ruler
.author
Thad Floryan
Chad Netzer
Dave Schreiber
.description
Ruler is a small tool used in the measurement and constraint of text.
originally conceived as a tool for insuring that filenames didn't exceed
the Amiga's 30 character limit, it is nevertheless useful in any situation
where the number of characters in a line of text needs to be counted.
.type
Workbench Tool
.version
5.00
.source
Full C source included.
.distribution
Copyright but Freely Redistributable
.short
Count chars on text line, V5.00, C src.
